Ad Text:
Insighture is a leading technology consultancy that drives digital transformation for businesses worldwide. With a team of over 85 expert consultants, the company delivers tailored, high-impact strategies and solutions, enabling scalable product engineering. As an AWS partner, Insighture excels in co-integrated cloud services. It has collaborated with more than 50 clients globally, guiding them through cloud adoption, DevOps transformation, enterprise modernisation, and more.

The team’s expertise spans Cloud-Native Development, Solutions Architecture, UI/UX, Quality Engineering, Data Engineering, AI/ML, and DevSecOps. These capabilities empower businesses to achieve impactful and innovative outcomes.

In 2024, Insighture achieved ISO certification and was recognised as a Great Place to Work, earning three prestigious awards: Best Workplace in Sri Lanka, Best Workplace for Technology, and Best Workplace for Young People. Insighture's technology and expertise are embedded in the work of internationally recognised care providers, global freight operations, child protection systems, and health tech platforms across Australia, the UK, and Singapore.


We are seeking a motivated and detail-oriented MS Dynamics Consultant with AWS for a 1 year contract.

Qualifications:

Proven experience as a Solution Architect with a focus on cloud-based contact center solutions.

Expertise in AWS services, particularly AWS Connect, and experience with related services like Lambda, DynamoDB, and API Gateway.

Strong knowledge of Microsoft Dynamics 365, including its capabilities for customer service and contact center management.

Experience with integration technologies like APIs, webhooks, and middleware platforms.

Solid understanding of cloud security best practices and compliance requirements.

Excellent communication, collaboration, and problem-solving skills.

Experience with Agile development methodologies is often preferred.

Responsibilities:

Solution Design: Develop comprehensive architectural designs for integrating AWS Connect with Microsoft Dynamics 365, considering call flows, data integration, security, and scalability.

Technical Leadership: Provide technical guidance and mentorship to development teams throughout the project lifecycle.

Integration Expertise: Design and implement robust integrations between AWS Connect and Dynamics 365, utilizing APIs, webhooks, and other relevant technologies.

Cloud Architecture: Define and implement cloud infrastructure on AWS, including compute, storage, networking, and security services, specifically tailored for contact center solutions.

Security Best Practices: Ensure the solution adheres to strict security guidelines and compliance standards, protecting sensitive customer data.

Performance Optimization: Optimize the solution for performance, scalability, and cost-effectiveness, leveraging AWS services effectively.

Stakeholder Collaboration: Work closely with business stakeholders, development teams, and other technical experts to gather requirements and ensure alignment on the solution design.

Documentation: Create and maintain detailed architectural documentation, including diagrams, specifications, and deployment procedures.

Troubleshooting and Support: Assist in troubleshooting complex issues and providing ongoing support for the integrated solution.

Staying Current: Maintain a strong understanding of the latest advancements in AWS Connect, Dynamics 365, and related technologies.
